The paper deals with mechanism design and auctions, which are topics typically studied in the game theory (cs.GT) and economics (cs.EC) sub-categories of computer science. The use of the VCG mechanism and its limitations also suggest a connection to optimization (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the technical aspects of the paper, including the use of combinatorial equivalence and differential equations, suggest a possible connection to machine learning (cs.LG).
